rComments: He literally tells you the exact slides he tests from. All you have to do is read the abstracts and pick out the main idea. I feel people don't like him because he actually tests on theories and studies rather then just definitions, but it's really not difficult. He is kind and cares about his students. He tries to make class fun by telling jokes.

Literally the worst professor Ive ever had in my life. HORRIBLE. like there are no words to describe how bad this prof is. The man has a good heart tho, i'ill give him that. He's really sweet outside of class or whatever but the man does not know how to conduct a class. Drop the class while you still can sis. Save your time and your GPA!

Im shocked by the amount of bad reviews this prof has. Definitely feel as though these students didnt do readings or study. He tries to make the class as accessible as possible for students by providing all required materials on the slides (which are posted online). He goes above and beyond to help students who want to do well. One of my favs. :)

This is probably the worst layout of a class that Ive ever been in. Reads abstracts to you, and then tests you on your ability to memorize abstracts and articles. Wasnt hard, but a completely pointless course, so dont expect to actually learn anything.

Although he has a lot of bad reviews, this class was basically one of the easiest classes I've ever taken. He is a super sweet prof who you can tell really cares about his students. His midterms and exams are super easy.

Nice guy, but terrible professor. Instead of teaching he provides a pointless amount of abstracts, and reads them out loud in class instead of teaching course material. Very hard to follow announcements posted, and what you are expected to do. Take social motivation with a different professor in order to actually learn about social motivation.

His lectures are absolutely pointless, all he does is read articles to the class. The midterm has nothing to do with what we learned at all, and he expects us to memorize 3 articles and be able to summarize them on the final without bringing any outside material in at all. Don't take this course with him.
Very dry material and constantly goes off topic. Half of what is brought up in class is not even tested. No organization to the course whatsoever.

I showed up to about 2 classes but Aced the online tests and essay. Just read the textbook and you will do fine! He's a nice, funny in-an-awkward-way prof, but he's so disorganized and rambles off about unrelated stories. Tests and exams are fair and simple.

If you think you can do this, you can't. He is disorganized and skips through slides. You won't remember a single word. Please listen to this warning!

The professor is a really nice guy, but he rambles in all of his lectures and skips around on his slides, often skipping huge chunks & is very inconsistent about what will be covered in class. Overall the lectures are really confusing but his testing methods are really easy if you're good at memorization

I am so shook that this prof has bad ratings. He is a really nice guy. I retook the class with Laliberte and learned more in her intro lecture than in a whole semester with Bentley. Very sweet man but I learned nothing

He takes ten thousand years to get his points across but most times when he's talking you can't even figure out what point he was trying to get across even when he's done. Very difficult to listen to because he talks slowly and is vague. Tries to be funny which is a waste of time and focus considering he talks slowly. Reads from textbook in class.

He's great as a person but doesn't teach the material in class, he discusses it, and heavily focuses on articles and extra readings. textbook was easy to understand, but the lectures confused me. I came to lectures for participation activities and to "check in" lol but studied on my own and got with an average grade. Read the textbook
regrets
Rambles on and on without getting the point across. As a part time prof he should be hetter than this.

One of the worst professors I've ever had, would avoid all courses in the future if he is teaching them. TERRIBLE!! He jumps between different lectures and powerpoints which makes following along in class difficult. Mentions random articles and names that you don't even need to know for the exam. WORST PROF EVER. GET OUT NOW.

Terrible teacher. Bad jokes. Get ready to teach yourself. The textbook is long and boring. He rambles and goes off topic. Hard marker. Don't do it! Run away! Totally ruined the subject and I didn't learn anything. Waste of time and money.

Professor Bentley is by far the worst professor I have ever had at UOttawa. Listen up... Here's an unemotional report about this professor. This is the worst prof ever. You learn nothing in his class. Most people are failing or barely passing. His midterms are terrible. Avoid this prof at all costs!

THIS TEACHER IS ABSOLUTELY AWFUL!!!! So unclear about his expectations, he is slide shows make no sense or relate to the book readings ether. NEVER TAKE A CLASS WITH HIM! He is a absolutely terrible professor. He rambles on about nothing and mostly takes about articles that he posts online non-stop. Nice guy but VERY unclear. I took Cross-cultural psychology thinking it would be about psychology in different cultures, but I honestly have no idea what he's rambling on about. WORST PROF I HAVE HAD YET!! He rambles on and on about stuff that has absolutely nothing to do with the course content. Very hard to follow his lecturing and slides are terrible/useful/unorganized. Do not take a class with him!!!!

he is a very nice person, and makes lame jokes that kind of make you laugh anyway. he is also a very easy marker. and easy 90. BUT he RAMBLES ON AND ON. download the slides from online, review them, but don't bother going to class -- you learn nothing and it's a waste of time.
